{"title":"Javascript Optimizations","link":"https://www.adamkoch.com/2010/11/24/javascript-optimizations/","pubDate":"Wed, 24 Nov 2010 15:05:07 +0000","dc:creator":"admin","guid":[{"_":"http://www.adamkoch.com/?p=1881","$":{"isPermaLink":"false"}}],"description":[""],"content:encoded":"I was looking at <a href=\"http://twitter.com/kangax\">kangax</a>'s <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/closure-compiler/issues/detail?id=36&amp;can=1&amp;q=increment&amp;colspec=ID%20Type%20Status%20Priority%20Component%20Owner%20Summary\">suggestions</a> for <a href=\"http://code.google.com/closure/compiler/\">Google Closure</a> compression techniques and I wanted to know how <a href=\"http://github.com/mishoo/UglifyJS/\">UglifyJS</a> handled it.\r\n\r\nInput:<code>\r\nvar i = 10000,\r\nj = 0.1,\r\nk = /[\\w]/,\r\nm = new Array(1, 2, 3);\r\nthrow 0.1;</code>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://closure-compiler.appspot.com/home\">Closure</a>:\r\n<code>var i=1E4,j=0.1,k=/[\\w]/,m=[1,2,3];throw 0.1;</code>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://marijnhaverbeke.nl/uglifyjs\">UglifyJS</a>:\r\n<code>var i=1e4,j=.1,k=/[\\w]/,m=new Array(1,2,3);throw.1</code>\r\n\r\nInteresting that <a href=\"http://github.com/mishoo/UglifyJS/\">UglifyJS</a> doesn't compress the Array declaration, but does compress 2 other statements that <a href=\"http://code.google.com/closure/compiler/\">Google Closure</a> doesn't/won't.\r\n\r\nIn UglifyJS's <a href=\"https://github.com/mishoo/UglifyJS/#readme\">README</a> it states that Google Closure \"runs terribly slow\". Why is this an issue? Won't you only compress when pushing to prod?","excerpt:encoded":"","wp:post_id":"1881","wp:post_date":"2010-11-24 09:05:07","wp:post_date_gmt":"2010-11-24 15:05:07","wp:post_modified":["2012-05-29 10:48:54"],"wp:post_modified_gmt":["2012-05-29 16:48:54"],"wp:comment_status":["open"],"wp:ping_status":["open"],"wp:post_name":"javascript-optimizations","wp:status":"publish","wp:post_parent":["0"],"wp:menu_order":["0"],"wp:post_type":"post","wp:post_password":[""],"wp:is_sticky":["0"],"category":[{"_":"closure","$":{"domain":"post_tag","nicename":"closure"}},{"_":"javascript","$":{"domain":"post_tag","nicename":"javascript"}},{"_":"linkedin","$":{"domain":"post_tag","nicename":"linkedin"}},{"_":"Professional","$":{"domain":"category","nicename":"professional"}},{"_":"uglifyjs","$":{"domain":"post_tag","nicename":"uglifyjs"}}],"wp:postmeta":[{"wp:meta_key":["aktt_notify_twitter"],"wp:meta_value":["no"]},{"wp:meta_key":["_edit_last"],"wp:meta_value":["1"]},{"wp:meta_key":["h5bp_link_url"],"wp:meta_value":[""]},{"wp:meta_key":["_jetpack_related_posts_cache"],"wp:meta_value":["a:1:{s:32:\"8f6677c9d6b0f903e98ad32ec61f8deb\";a:2:{s:7:\"expires\";i:1627637804;s:7:\"payload\";a:3:{i:0;a:1:{s:2:\"id\";i:1857;}i:1;a:1:{s:2:\"id\";i:2904;}i:2;a:1:{s:2:\"id\";i:1730;}}}}"]}],"wp:comment":[{"wp:comment_id":["688"],"wp:comment_author":["Mihai Bazon"],"wp:comment_author_email":["mihai.bazon@gmail.com"],"wp:comment_author_url":["http://mihai.bazon.net/blog"],"wp:comment_author_IP":["82.50.45.207"],"wp:comment_date":["2010-11-29 01:48:39"],"wp:comment_date_gmt":["2010-11-29 07:48:39"],"wp:comment_content":["Ah, good catch on new Array()!  I'll push a fix for this soon.\r\n\r\nIt's not that I'm minifying JavaScript on the fly, but I'm rather impatient.  Why wait 6 seconds when I can only wait one? ;-)"],"wp:comment_approved":["1"],"wp:comment_type":["comment"],"wp:comment_parent":["0"],"wp:comment_user_id":["0"]},{"wp:comment_id":["686"],"wp:comment_author":["Zach Leatherman"],"wp:comment_author_email":["zachleatherman@gmail.com"],"wp:comment_author_url":["http://www.zachleat.com/"],"wp:comment_author_IP":["68.13.117.221"],"wp:comment_date":["2010-11-24 18:55:52"],"wp:comment_date_gmt":["2010-11-25 00:55:52"],"wp:comment_content":["I've heard some old wives tales that some have their system set up to do on demand minifying.  Never witnessed this in the wild, however."],"wp:comment_approved":["1"],"wp:comment_type":["comment"],"wp:comment_parent":["0"],"wp:comment_user_id":["0"]},{"wp:comment_id":["1198"],"wp:comment_author":["Zach Leatherman"],"wp:comment_author_email":["zachleatherman@gmail.com"],"wp:comment_author_url":["http://www.zachleat.com/"],"wp:comment_author_IP":["72.37.9.218"],"wp:comment_date":["2011-07-11 11:57:00"],"wp:comment_date_gmt":["2011-07-11 17:57:00"],"wp:comment_content":["Also, I'm minifying multiple files in my build process. Takes FOREVER. Would love to use Uglify to speed it up."],"wp:comment_approved":["1"],"wp:comment_type":["comment"],"wp:comment_parent":["0"],"wp:comment_user_id":["0"],"wp:commentmeta":[{"wp:meta_key":["akismet_result"],"wp:meta_value":["false"]},{"wp:meta_key":["akismet_history"],"wp:meta_value":["a:4:{s:4:\"time\";s:13:\"1310407020.32\";s:7:\"message\";s:28:\"Akismet cleared this comment\";s:5:\"event\";s:9:\"check-ham\";s:4:\"user\";s:0:\"\";}"]}]}],"tidyCategory":"Professional","tidyTags":["closure","javascript","linkedin","uglifyjs"]}

